Doc Spatz, let's not lose sight of the fact that there is more to life than Viet Nam.  I love a beautiful sunset... how about You?<br><br>
I can love you for MANY reasons Doc... I could kick your butt for only a FEW.  Lop sided argument.<br><br>
You and I agreed to help one another.  We can begin by helping ourselves.  Divesting oneself of anger is a good place to start.  I am sorry that I went to Viet Nam but I am glad that I went to Viet Nam...I am sorry that you didn't go to Viet Nam... But, I'm glad you didn't have to go.  Somewhere in there lies a small patch of Sacred Earth where we can commend one another instead of condemn each other.<br><br>
Radical warriors had the same problem.. Some were viewed as blood thirsty, ego driven..mad men.... Others were looked upon as weak old women with no courage, always wanting to talk.  Between those two extremes lay a path that most good warriors followed... Patience sometimes...Power sometimes...Prudence always!<br><br>
Hang Tough, Wharf Rat..<br><br>
Field Rat Six...on your wing
